Updated: May 9, 2016 11:49 IST
Tiger Shroff.
Photo: Rajneesh Londhe
Actor Tiger Shroff has rubbished reports that he has signed a movie to be directed by filmmaker Subhash Ghai.
There were reports that Ghai had signed the Baaghi star as a lead in his comeback film.
When asked about this, Tiger said, “I haven’t signed anything with him.
We have been talking since a long time but nothing has really come out.
Working with him would be great for me.
He is not going to benefit much but I will get to learn a lot.”
Tiger, who made his debut in 2014 with Heropanti , was earlier supposed to be launched by Ghai.
Interestingly, the Taal filmmaker had launched Tiger’s father, Jackie Shroff as a leading man in Hero .
Known for films like Karz , Ram Lakhan and Pardes , the 71-year-old director last helmed Kaanchi: The Unbreakable , the same year Tiger made his debut.
Meanwhile, Tiger will be next seen in A Flying Jatt .
